        "title": "How to show index not the element",
        "body": "<p>Hi im trying to show the index of the array not the element this is part of my code so far:<\/p>\n\n<pre><code>int randomInt2 = randomGenerator.nextInt(15)+1;\ndouble [] distances = new double [randomInt2];\n\nArrays.sort(distances);// sorts array from highest to lowest        \nfor (double val : distances) {\nSystem.out.println(\"[\"+val+\"],\");\n}\n\nSystem.out.println(\"The Nearest to point 1 is point: \");\n<\/code><\/pre>\n\n<p>Each index holds an value between 1-1000 but i do not want to show the value i want to show the index so that I can show what indexes are closest to point 1 (which is 0) \nSorry if im not being clear and if you need me to explain more then I am happy to<\/p>\n",
